            "content": {
                "raw": "Thanks! :)\n\nI'm not sure if it should REPLACE the skeleton. I suppose it could, since I kept the comments from the skeleton, so users will know what they need to do. On the other hand, having a skeleton, which is a clean and empty template, is useful.\n\nAh, yes. Sorry I forgot about tests. I'll add those. Do you have some suggestions as to the type of test to include? What do the other frontends do? Check that the metadata is read in correctly, I suppose? Is there a testing infrastructure for checking that a generated plot is correct?\n\nYes, I'll update the copyright years. Oops on that front. :)",
                "html": "<p>Thanks! :)</p>\n<p>I'm not sure if it should REPLACE the skeleton. I suppose it could, since I kept the comments from the skeleton, so users will know what they need to do. On the other hand, having a skeleton, which is a clean and empty template, is useful.</p>\n<p>Ah, yes. Sorry I forgot about tests. I'll add those. Do you have some suggestions as to the type of test to include? What do the other frontends do? Check that the metadata is read in correctly, I suppose? Is there a testing infrastructure for checking that a generated plot is correct?</p>\n<p>Yes, I'll update the copyright years. Oops on that front. :)</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
