            "content": {
                "raw": "Most of the frontends use the answer testing infrastructure. There's more documentation about that here: http://yt-project.org/docs/dev/developing/testing.html#answer-testing\n\nThere is some infrastructure for tests that generate plots (using the answer testing infrastructure) but it would probably be better to take a look at the existing answer tests in some of the frontends. FLASH and Boxlib would probably good places to look.",
                "html": "<p>Most of the frontends use the answer testing infrastructure. There's more documentation about that here: <a href=\"http://yt-project.org/docs/dev/developing/testing.html#answer-testing\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://yt-project.org/docs/dev/developing/testing.html#answer-testing</a></p>\n<p>There is some infrastructure for tests that generate plots (using the answer testing infrastructure) but it would probably be better to take a look at the existing answer tests in some of the frontends. FLASH and Boxlib would probably good places to look.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
